This paper discusses privacy enforcement in the context of Internet of Things (IoT) smart objects. The paper focuses on the compliance check of user individual privacy preferences, which falls under the category of security and privacy (cs.CR). The paper also mentions the need for high-speed data processing and analytics, which could fall under information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the decentralization of data management, which could fall under the categories of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
